webpackJsonp([0xfb5479a49784],{370:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{page:{title:"QSS Help",body:{processed:'<h2 id="change-language">Change Language</h2>\n\n<p>This feature Works in Windows and Programs that support Windows language settings.</p>\n\n<p>Changing the language will change the Windows language setting. Applications that support the Windows Language setting will also change. You may need to restart some browsers and applications to see the language changes.</p>\n\n<p>Note: Changing to a different language will not change the language in any documents you open. If you need to translate text and documents, you may want to try one of the following free services:</p>\n\n<ul><li><a href="https://translate.google.com/">Google Translate</a></li>\n\t<li><a href="https://www.bing.com/translator">Microsoft Translate (Bing)</a></li>\n\t<li><a href="http://www.online-translator.com/">PROMT online translator</a></li>\n\t<li><a href="http://www.worldlingo.com/en/products_services/worldlingo_translator.html">WorldLingo translation</a></li>\n\t<li><a href="www.reverso.net/text_translation.aspx">Reverso Translation</a></li>\n\t<li><a href="https://www.onlinedoctranslator.com/translationform">DocTranslator</a></li>\n</ul><p>(Links are provided for your convenience and are not an endorsement of any particular service.)</p>\n\n<h2 id="app-text-zoom">App / Text Zoom</h2>\n\n<p>The “App / Text Zoom” menu lets you zoom in and out while working in individual applications. It works in many applications, including Edge, Chrome, Firefox, Word, Excel and Adobe Reader. You will zoom in and out in the last application you used.</p>\n\n<p>Note: As a shortcut, you can press Ctrl and move the mouse scroll wheel up or down to also zoom in or out in applications. Similarly, the Ctrl key can be pressed at the same time as the minus key (-) to zoom out or the plus key (+) to zoom in.</p>\n\n<p>If you want to zoom in or out on everything on the screen, use the “Screen Zoom” menu instead.</p>\n\n<h2 id="screen-zoom">Screen Zoom</h2>\n\n<p>The “Screen Zoom” menu lets you zoom in and out on the entire desktop and everything on it. Everything on the screen will get bigger or smaller by the same amount.</p>\n\n<ul><li>To zoom in, press the “larger” button with the "+" sign.</li>\n\t<li>To zoom out, press the “smaller” button with the "-" sign.</li>\n</ul><h2 id="youtube-captions">YouTube Captions</h2>\n\n<p>This feature turns on captions on YouTube videos imbedded within text on a page. Note: This feature will not function on the YouTube website.</p>\n\n<h2 id="high-low-contrast">High / Low Contrast</h2>\n\n<p>The “High / Low Contrast” menu has a list of high contrast and low contrast settings. Choosing a setting will change how Windows looks.</p>\n\n<p>The setting will also apply to web pages viewed in Edge and Chrome.</p>\n\n<p>High and low contrast setting can be used to make things easier to read or view for some people.</p>\n\n<h2 id="read-aloud">Read Aloud</h2>\n\n<p>This feature will read the text aloud on the page while highlighting each word.</p>\n\n<ul><li>To read starting from the top of the page,\n\t<ul><li>use the “read aloud” feature, click the read button. The read button is the right-pointing arrow located in the upper left-hand side of the screen.</li>\n\t\t<li>To pause/stop the reading, press the pause button, also located in the upper left-hand side of the page.</li>\n\t</ul></li>\n</ul><ul><li>To have a specific block of text read aloud rather than the whole page of text,\n\t<ul><li>highlight the preferred lines of text and then press the read button that appears next to the selected text.</li>\n\t\t<li>Click anywhere on the screen to stop the reading.</li>\n\t</ul></li>\n</ul><h2 id="more">More</h2>\n\n<p>Watch this space for more Morphic buttons as they are developed.</p>\n\n<p>You can also use this button to learn more about additional features designed to customize your computer to your specific needs and preferences.</p>\n\n<h2 id="save">Save</h2>\n\n<p>Use this button to save the current setting to the cloud - so that you can have them automatically applied to any other Morphic Enabled computer when you sign in to Morphic or use a KEY.</p>\n\n<p>To get a sign-in or key go to Morphic.World and set up an account.</p>\n\n<h2 id="undo">Undo</h2>\n\n<p>To undo your last Quick Set Strip selection, click the “undo” button.</p>\n\n<h2 id="close">Close</h2>\n\n<p>To close out the Quick Set Strip, click on the “x” located in the center of the close box.</p>\n\n<p>Morphic will still be running in the background.</p>\n\n<h2 id="reset-morphic">RESET MORPHIC</h2>\n\n<p>You can reset a Morphic enabled computer at any time by right-clicking Morphic icon in the bottom right of your screen -- and selecting “Reset Morphic”</p>',value:'<h2 id="change-language">Change Language</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This feature Works in Windows and Programs that support Windows language settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Changing the language will change the Windows language setting. Applications that support the Windows Language setting will also change. You may need to restart some browsers and applications to see the language changes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: Changing to a different language will not change the language in any documents you open. If you need to translate text and documents, you may want to try one of the following free services:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><a href="https://translate.google.com/">Google Translate</a></li>\r\n\t<li><a href="https://www.bing.com/translator">Microsoft Translate (Bing)</a></li>\r\n\t<li><a href="http://www.online-translator.com/">PROMT online translator</a></li>\r\n\t<li><a href="http://www.worldlingo.com/en/products_services/worldlingo_translator.html">WorldLingo translation</a></li>\r\n\t<li><a href="www.reverso.net/text_translation.aspx">Reverso Translation</a></li>\r\n\t<li><a href="https://www.onlinedoctranslator.com/translationform">DocTranslator</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>(Links are provided for your convenience and are not an endorsement of any particular service.)</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="app-text-zoom">App / Text Zoom</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The “App / Text Zoom” menu lets you zoom in and out while working in individual applications. It works in many applications, including Edge, Chrome, Firefox, Word, Excel and Adobe Reader. You will zoom in and out in the last application you used.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: As a shortcut, you can press Ctrl and move the mouse scroll wheel up or down to also zoom in or out in applications. Similarly, the Ctrl key can be pressed at the same time as the minus key (-) to zoom out or the plus key (+) to zoom in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to zoom in or out on everything on the screen, use the “Screen Zoom” menu instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="screen-zoom">Screen Zoom</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The “Screen Zoom” menu lets you zoom in and out on the entire desktop and everything on it. Everything on the screen will get bigger or smaller by the same amount.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>To zoom in, press the “larger” button with the "+" sign.</li>\r\n\t<li>To zoom out, press the “smaller” button with the "-" sign.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="youtube-captions">YouTube Captions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This feature turns on captions on YouTube videos imbedded within text on a page. Note: This feature will not function on the YouTube website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="high-low-contrast">High / Low Contrast</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The “High / Low Contrast” menu has a list of high contrast and low contrast settings. Choosing a setting will change how Windows looks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The setting will also apply to web pages viewed in Edge and Chrome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High and low contrast setting can be used to make things easier to read or view for some people.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="read-aloud">Read Aloud</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This feature will read the text aloud on the page while highlighting each word.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>To read starting from the top of the page,\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>use the “read aloud” feature, click the read button. The read button is the right-pointing arrow located in the upper left-hand side of the screen.</li>\r\n\t\t<li>To pause/stop the reading, press the pause button, also located in the upper left-hand side of the page.</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>To have a specific block of text read aloud rather than the whole page of text,\r\n\t<ul>\r\n\t\t<li>highlight the preferred lines of text and then press the read button that appears next to the selected text.</li>\r\n\t\t<li>Click anywhere on the screen to stop the reading.</li>\r\n\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="more">More</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Watch this space for more Morphic buttons as they are developed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also use this button to learn more about additional features designed to customize your computer to your specific needs and preferences.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="save">Save</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Use this button to save the current setting to the cloud - so that you can have them automatically applied to any other Morphic Enabled computer when you sign in to Morphic or use a KEY.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get a sign-in or key go to Morphic.World and set up an account.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="undo">Undo</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To undo your last Quick Set Strip selection, click the “undo” button.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="close">Close</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To close out the Quick Set Strip, click on the “x” located in the center of the close box.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Morphic will still be running in the background.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 id="reset-morphic">RESET MORPHIC</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can reset a Morphic enabled computer at any time by right-clicking Morphic icon in the bottom right of your screen -- and selecting “Reset Morphic”</p>\r\n'}}},pathContext:{alias:"/help/qsshelp"}}}});
